article.description: Jordan Price and Tony Washington turned in double-doubles and La Salle upset St. Bonaventure 71-64 to snap a 10-game losing streak Wednesday night.
article.headline: La Salle upsets Bonnies 71-64, snaps 10-game losing streak
article.linkText: La Salle upsets Bonnies 71-64, snaps 10-game losing streak
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Jordan Price and Tony Washington turned in double-doubles and La Salle upset St. Bonaventure 71-64 to snap a 10-game losing streak Wednesday night. Marcus Posley's 3-pointer gave St. Bonaventure a one-point lead but the Explorers took control in the final two minutes with a basket from Washington and two by Price before La Salle added three free throws. Price had 18 points, 10 rebounds plus six assists and Washington added 10 points and 12 rebounds for the Explorers (6-18, 2-11 Atlantic 10). It was the first double-double of the season for Price and Washington's fourth. Cleon Roberts added 14 points and Johnnie Shuler 12. La Salle outrebounded the Bonnies 41-27. Posley made five 3-pointers and scored 21 points for the Bonnies (17-7, 9-4), who shot just 37 percent and saw a five-game winning streak end. Dion Wright added 16 points and Jaylen Adams 12.
